<meta name="Description" content="Biological Warfare is a program that will generate assembly source code  for a fully functional virus according to the specifications that the user  gives it. When Biological Warfare is run, it will give the user a menu with  a list of options pertaining to the virus. The user can manipulate the options  as directed to create the virus to his specifications.  Following are the options of version 0.90B:      Text - Any text that has to appear within the virus, up to 60 characters.    Resident - Specifies whether virus will be resident in memory or not.    Infect - Either COM, EXE, or both.    Encryption - Specifies if the virus will feature encryption.    INT 24 Handler - Specifies if the virus will steal DOS's critical error handler to avoid write protect errors.    Anti-Trace - Specifies if the virus will includes routines to thwart trivial debugging or tracing.    Maximum Size - If selected, the virus will not infect any .COM file too large for it.    Traversal - Specifies if the virus will move upwards in the directory tree.    Infections/run - Maximum number of files to infect each run.    Avoid COMMAND - Specifies if the virus will infect COMMAND.COM.    EXE Marker - Two characters used to indicate an infected .EXE file.    Overlay check - Specifies that the virus will not infect .EXE files with internal overlays.    DirStealth - Hides the file size increases from a directory listing.  All infected files have their seconds field set to the given number. Absence  this number indicates that no directory stealth function will be included.  (Resident viruses only)    Infect on - Specifies if the virus has to infect when opening a file, executing a file or both.    Activate - Virus will include space for an activation routine in the code.     More directory stealth - In conjunction with directory stealth this will  make the increase in file size invisible from any file managing programs  in addition to a DIR command.    Version 1.00 added the following:      Encryption, both standard and basic polymorphic (via the Biological Warfare Mutation Engine)    Time stamp - This is used by either directory stealth or polymorphism.    Biological Warfare Mutation Engine      The BWME is a very basic polymorphic encryption engine that will make the  virus more difficult to scan. It's size is 609 bytes."/>
