<div class="s2"> [<a href="/vx.php?id=tb06">Previous</a>] [<a href="/vx.php?id=tidx">Index</a>] [<a href="/vx.php?id=tb04">Next</a>] <h1> Biological Warefare Virus Creation Kit</h1><p><strong>Author: Mnemonix</strong></p><p>Biological Warfare is a program that will generate assembly source code
for a fully functional virus according to the specifications that the user
gives it. When Biological Warfare is run, it will give the user a menu with
a list of options pertaining to the virus. The user can manipulate the options
as directed to create the virus to his specifications.</p>
<p>Following are the options of version 0.90B:</p>
<ol type="A">
<li>Text - Any text that has to appear within the virus, up to 60 characters.</li>
<li>Resident - Specifies whether virus will be resident in memory or not.</li>
<li>Infect - Either COM, EXE, or both.</li>
<li>Encryption - Specifies if the virus will feature encryption.</li>
<li>INT 24 Handler - Specifies if the virus will steal DOS's critical error handler to avoid write protect errors.</li>
<li>Anti-Trace - Specifies if the virus will includes routines to thwart trivial debugging or tracing.</li>
<li>Maximum Size - If selected, the virus will not infect any .COM file too large for it.</li>
<li>Traversal - Specifies if the virus will move upwards in the directory tree.</li>
<li>Infections/run - Maximum number of files to infect each run.</li>
<li>Avoid COMMAND - Specifies if the virus will infect COMMAND.COM.</li>
<li>EXE Marker - Two characters used to indicate an infected .EXE file.</li>
<li>Overlay check - Specifies that the virus will not infect .EXE files with internal overlays.</li>
<li>DirStealth - Hides the file size increases from a directory listing.
All infected files have their seconds field set to the given number. Absence
this number indicates that no directory stealth function will be included.
(Resident viruses only)</li>
<li>Infect on - Specifies if the virus has to infect when opening a file, executing a file or both.</li>
<li>Activate - Virus will include space for an activation routine in the code. </li>
<li>More directory stealth - In conjunction with directory stealth this will
make the increase in file size invisible from any file managing programs
in addition to a DIR command.</li>
</ol>
<p>Version 1.00 added the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Encryption, both standard and basic polymorphic (via the Biological Warfare Mutation Engine)</li>
<li>Time stamp - This is used by either directory stealth or polymorphism.</li>
<li>Biological Warfare Mutation Engine
<p>The BWME is a very basic polymorphic encryption engine that will make the
virus more difficult to scan. It's size is 609 bytes.</p></li>
</ul>
